# The voice she actually uses lives in voice/ and is tracked. Everything below
# is either third-party bulk or an experiment that lost.

# RVC: the library fork, its venv, and ~1.7 GB of weights, index and models.
voice-runtime/

# Her rendered audio — the replay cache and the lines she finished saying.
# Kept beside beni.db because that is what it is: runtime state, not code.
data/voice/

# Emotion anchors are cut from your local episode files by build_emotions.py —
# the manifest is tracked, the derived audio is not.
voice/clips/emotions/

# Dead ends, kept only until RVC has earned their disk space: the Piper
# fine-tune, the Qwen3-TTS models and venv, GPT-SoVITS. Nothing on the RVC
# path resolves in here, so this whole directory is safe to delete.
addons/

